properties.areaDesc: Coastal Waters from Point Pinos to Point Piedras Blancas California out to 10 nm
properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 14 at 3:37AM PST until January 16 at 9:00AM PST by NWS San Francisco CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Small Craft Advisory, northwest winds 15 to 25
kt with gusts up to 30 kt expected. For the Gale Watch,
southeast winds 25 to 35 kt with gusts up to 50 kt and seas 8
to 10 feet at 13 seconds possible.

* WHERE...Coastal Waters from Point Pinos to Point Piedras
Blancas California out to 10 nm.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, from 9 AM this morning to
9 PM PST this evening. For the Gale Watch, from late Wednesday
night through Thursday morning.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and seas.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 9 AM THIS MORNING TO 9 PM PST THIS EVENING... ...GALE WATCH IN EFFECT FROM LATE WEDNESDAY NIGHT THROUGH THURSDAY MORNING
